2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with MIMO systems, which are commonly used in wireless communication networks. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper involves signal processing techniques such as Tucker decomposition to reduce the dimensionality of the codebook. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with 3D MIMO systems, which are used in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a closed-form suboptimal solution to reduce the computational complexity in Tucker decomposition, which involves computational engineering concepts.
